label: Age Class
rdfs_comment: The age class, reproductive stage, life stage of the biological individual (e.g., juvenile, adult, eft, nymph, etc.).

label: Basis of Record
rdfs_comment: An abbreviation indicating whether the record represents an observation (O), living organism (L), specimen (S), germplasm/seed (G), etc.

label: Basis of Record
rdfs_comment: A description indicating whether the record represents an observation, tissue sample, living organism, voucher specimen, germplasm/seed, genetic information, etc.

label: Bounding Box
rdfs_comment: This access point provides a mechanism for performing searches using a bounding box. A Bounding Box element is not typically present in the database, but rather is derived from the Latitude and Longitude columns by the data provider

label: Bounding Box
rdfs_comment: This access point provides a mechanism for performing searches using a bounding box. A Bounding Box element is not typically present in the database, but rather is derived from the DecimalLatitude and DecimalLongitude columns by the data provider.

label: Catalog Number
rdfs_comment: A unique alphanumeric value which identifies an individual record within the collection. It is recommended that this value provides a key by which the actual specimen can be identified. If the specimen has several items such as various types of preparation, this value should identify the individual component of the specimen

label: Catalog Number Numeric
rdfs_comment: The CatalogNumber as a numeric value, if applicable. Allows searching on numeric ranges of CatalogNumbers.

label: Catalog Number Text
rdfs_comment: An alphanumeric value which identifies an individual cataloged item within the collection. It is recommended that this value provides a key by which the individual cataloged item can be identified.

label: Class
rdfs_comment: The class name of the organism

label: Class
rdfs_comment: The phylogenetic class to which the cataloged item belongs.

label: Collection Code
rdfs_comment: A unique alphanumeric value which identifies the collection within the institution

label: Collection Code
rdfs_comment: A unique alphanumeric value that identifies the collection within the institution in which the item is cataloged. This attribute must contain no spaces.

label: Collector
rdfs_comment: The name(s) of the collector(s) responsible for collection the specimen or taking the observation

label: Collector
rdfs_comment: The name(s) of the collector(s) of the original data for the cataloged item.

label: Collector Number
rdfs_comment: An identifying "number" (really a string) applied to specimens (in some disciplines) at the time of collection. Establishes a links different parts/preparations of a single specimen and between field notes and the specimen.

label: Collector Number
rdfs_comment: An identifying string applied to the cataloged item at the time of collection. Serves as a link between field notes and the cataloged items.

label: Continent Ocean
rdfs_comment: The continent or ocean from which a specimen was collected.

label: Continent Ocean
rdfs_comment: The full, unabbreviated name of the continent or ocean from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Coordinate Precision
rdfs_comment: An estimate of how tightly the collecting locality was specified; expressed as a distance, in meters, that corresponds to a radius around the latitude-longitude coordinates. Use NULL where precision is unknown, cannot be estimated, or is not applicable.

label: Coordinate Uncertainty In Meters
rdfs_comment: The upper limit of the distance (in meters) from the given latitude and longitude describing a circle within which the whole of the described locality must lie. Use NULL where the uncertainty is unknown, cannot be estimated, or is not applicable.

label: Country
rdfs_comment: The country or major political unit from which the specimen was collected. ISO 3166-1 (http://www.din.de/gremien/nas/nabd/iso3166ma/codlstp1/db_en.html) values should be used. Full country names are currently in use. A future recommendation is to use ISO3166-1 two letter codes or the full name when searching

label: Country
rdfs_comment: The full, unabbreviated name of the country or major political unit from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: County
rdfs_comment: The county (or shire, or next political region smaller than State / Province) from which the specimen was collected

label: County
rdfs_comment: The full, unabbreviated name of the county, shire, or municipality (i.e., the next smaller political region than StateProvince) from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Date Last Modified
rdfs_comment: ISO 8601 compliant stamp indicating the date and time in UTC(GMT) when the record was last modified. Example: the instant "November 5, 1994, 8:15:30 am, US Eastern Standard Time" would be represented as "1994-11-05T13:15:30Z" (see W3C Note on Date and Time Formats - http://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime). (What to do when this date-time is unknown? Use Date-Time first "published"?)

label: Date Last Modified
rdfs_comment: ISO 8601 date and time in UTC(GMT) when the record was last modified. Example: "November 5, 1994, 8:15:30 am, US Eastern Standard Time" would be "1994-11-05T13:15:30Z" (see http://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime).

label: Day Collected
rdfs_comment: The day of the month the specimen was collected from the field. Possible value ranges from 01..31 inclusive

label: Day Collected
rdfs_comment: The two digit day of the month in the Common Era calendar during which the cataloged item was collected from the field.

label: Day Identified
rdfs_comment: The day portion of the date when the Collection Item was identified; as two digits [01..31].

label: Day Identified
rdfs_comment: The two digit day of the month in the Common Era calendar during which the cataloged item was identified.

label: Decimal Latitude
rdfs_comment: The latitude of the location from which the cataloged item was collected, expressed in decimal degrees.

label: Decimal Longitude
rdfs_comment: The longitude of the location from which the cataloged item was collected, expressed in decimal degrees.

label: Family
rdfs_comment: The family name of the organism

label: Family
rdfs_comment: The phylogenetic family to which the cataloged item belongs.

label: Field Notes
rdfs_comment: A reference to, or flag marking the existence of notes taken in the field for the cataloged item.

label: Field Number
rdfs_comment: A "number" (really a string) created at collection time to identify all material that resulted from a collecting event.

label: Field Number
rdfs_comment: An identifying string applied to a set of material that resulted from a single collecting event.

label: Gen Bank Num
rdfs_comment: GenBank Accession number.

label: Genus
rdfs_comment: The genus name of the organism

label: Genus
rdfs_comment: The phylogenetic genus to which the cataloged item belongs.

label: Georef Method
rdfs_comment: A reference to the methods used for determining the coordinates and uncertainties.

label: Higher Geography
rdfs_comment: The combination of all geographic elements less specific than locality. "Like" query operations on this element will search for a substring in any of the higher geography attributes.

label: Higher Taxon
rdfs_comment: The combination of names of taxonomic ranks less specific than Genus. "Like" query operations on this element will search for a substring in any of the higher taxon attributes.

label: Horizontal Datum
rdfs_comment: The horizontal geodetic datum to which the DecimalLatitude and DecimalLongitude refer.

label: Identification Modifier
rdfs_comment: Additional information documenting the taxonomic determination of the cataloged item (e.g., "cf.", "aff.", "subspecies in question", etc.).

label: Identified By
rdfs_comment: The name(s) of the person(s) who applied the currently accepted Scientific Name to the Cataloged Item.

label: Identified By
rdfs_comment: The name(s) of the person(s) who applied the currently accepted ScientificName to the cataloged item.

label: Individual Count
rdfs_comment: The number of individuals present in the lot or container. Not an estimate of abundance or density at the collecting locality.

label: Individual Count
rdfs_comment: The number of individuals present in the lot or container referred to by the catalog number. Not an estimate of abundance or density at the collecting locality.

label: Institution Code
rdfs_comment: A "standard" code identifier that identifies the institution to which the collection belongs. No global registry exists for assigning institutional codes. Use the code that is "standard" in your discipline.

label: Institution Code
rdfs_comment: A code that identifies the institution to which the cataloged item belongs. No global registry exists for institutional codes; use the code that is "standard" in your discipline. This attribute must contain no spaces.

label: Island
rdfs_comment: The full, unabbreviated name of the island from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Island Group
rdfs_comment: The full, unabbreviated name of the island group from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Julian Day
rdfs_comment: The ordinal day of the year; i.e., the number of days since January 1 of the same year. (January 1 is Julian Day 1.)

label: Julian Day
rdfs_comment: The ordinal day of the year (i.e., the number of days since December 31 of the previous year; January 1 is Julian Day 1) on which the cataloged item was collected. May be derived from the YearCollected, MonthCollected, and DayCollected by the provider.

label: Kingdom
rdfs_comment: The kingdom to which the organism belongs

label: Kingdom
rdfs_comment: The phylogenetic kingdom to which the cataloged item belongs.

label: Latitude
rdfs_comment: The latitude of the location from which the specimen was collected. This value should be expressed in decimal degrees with a datum such as WGS-84

label: Lat Long Comments
rdfs_comment: Comments about the LatLong determination.

label: Locality
rdfs_comment: The locality description (place name plus optionally a displacement from the place name) from which the specimen was collected. Where a displacement from a location is provided, it should be in un-projected units of measurement

label: Locality
rdfs_comment: The description of the locality from which the cataloged item was collected, sans geographic information provided in other geographic fields.

label: Longitude
rdfs_comment: The longitude of the location from which the specimen was collected. This value should be expressed in decimal degrees with a datum such as WGS-84

label: Maximum Depth
rdfs_comment: The maximum distance in meters below the surface of the water at which the collection was made; all material collected was at most this deep. Positive below the surface, negative above (e.g. collecting above sea level in tidal areas).

label: Maximum Depth In Meters
rdfs_comment: The maximum distance in meters below the surface of the water at which the collection was made; all material collected was at most this deep. Positive below the surface, negative above (e.g., collecting above sea level in tidal areas).

label: Maximum Elevation
rdfs_comment: The maximum distance in meters above (positive) or below sea level of the collecting locality.

label: Maximum Elevation In Meters
rdfs_comment: The maximum distance in meters above (positive) or below sea level of the collecting locality.

label: Minimum Depth
rdfs_comment: The minimum distance in meters below the surface of the water at which the collection was made; all material collected was at least this deep. Positive below the surface, negative above (e.g. collecting above sea level in tidal areas).

label: Minimum Depth In Meters
rdfs_comment: The minimum distance in meters below the surface of the water at which the collection was made; all material collected was at least this deep. Positive below the surface, negative above (e.g., collecting above sea level in tidal areas).

label: Minimum Elevation
rdfs_comment: The minimum distance in meters above (positive) or below sea level of the collecting locality.

label: Minimum Elevation In Meters
rdfs_comment: The minimum distance in meters above (positive) or below sea level of the collecting locality.

label: Month Collected
rdfs_comment: The month of year the specimen was collected from the field. Possible values range from 01...12 inclusive

label: Month Collected
rdfs_comment: The two digit month of year in the Common Era calendar during which the cataloged item was collected from the field.

label: Month Identified
rdfs_comment: The month portion of the date when the Collection Item was identified; as two digits [01..12].

label: Month Identified
rdfs_comment: The two digit month in the Common Era calendar during which the cataloged item was identified.

label: Notes
rdfs_comment: Free text notes attached to the specimen record

label: Order
rdfs_comment: The order name of the organism

label: Order
rdfs_comment: The phylogenetic order to which the cataloged item belongs.

label: Original Coordinate System
rdfs_comment: The name of the system in which the original geographic coordinates were recorded (e.g., "decimal degrees", "degrees minutes seconds", "UTM", etc.).

label: Other Catalog Numbers
rdfs_comment: A list of previous or alternative fully qualified catalog numbers of the cataloged item whether in the current collection or in any other.

label: Phylum
rdfs_comment: The phylum (or division) to which the organism belongs

label: Phylum
rdfs_comment: The phylogenetic phylum (or division) to which the cataloged item belongs.

label: Preparations
rdfs_comment: A concatenated list of preparations and preservation methods (skin, skull, skeleton, whole animal (ETOH), slide, etc.) for the cataloged item.

label: Preparation Type
rdfs_comment: The type of preparation (skin. slide, etc). Probably best to add this as a record element rather than access point. Should be a list of preparations for a single collection record.

label: Previous Catalog Number
rdfs_comment: The previous (fully qualified) catalog number of the Cataloged Item if the item earlier identified by another Catalog Number, either in the current catalog or another Institution / catalog. A fully qualified Catalog Number is preceded by Institution Code and Collection Code, with a space separating the each subelement. Referencing a previous Catalog Number does not imply that a record for the referenced item is or is not present in the corresponding catalog, or even that the referenced catalog still exists. This access point is intended to provide a way to retrieve this record by previously used identifier, which may used in the literature. In future versions of this schema this attribute should be set-valued.

label: Related Cataloged Items
rdfs_comment: The fully qualified identifier (Institution Code + " " + Collection Code + " " + Catalog Number) of the related Cataloged Item, preceded by the nature of the relationship (e.g., (sibling of) MVZ Mamm 1234).

label: Related Cataloged Item
rdfs_comment: The fully qualified identifier of a related Catalog Item (a reference to another specimen); Institution Code, Collection Code, and Catalog Number of the related Cataloged Item, where a space separates the three subelements.

label: Relationship Type
rdfs_comment: A named or coded valued that identifies the kind relationship between this Collection Item and the referenced Collection Item. Named values include: "parasite of", "epiphyte on", "progeny of", etc. In future versions of this schema this attribute should be set-valued.

label: Remarks
rdfs_comment: Free text comments accompanying the cataloged item record.

label: Scientific Name
rdfs_comment: The full name of lowest level taxon the Cataloged Item can be identified as a member of; includes genus name, specific epithet, and subspecific epithet (zool.) or infraspecific rank abbreviation, and infraspecific epithet (bot.) Use name of suprageneric taxon (e.g., family name) if Cataloged Item cannot be identified to genus, species, or infraspecific taxon.

label: Scientific Name
rdfs_comment: The full name of lowest level taxon to which the cataloged item can be identified (e.g., genus name, specific epithet, subspecific epithet, etc.).

label: Scientific Name Author
rdfs_comment: The author of a scientific name. Author string as applied to the accepted name. Can be more than one author (concatenated string). Should be formatted according to the conventions of the applicable taxonomic discipline.

label: Scientific Name Author
rdfs_comment: The author of the ScientificName. Can be more than one author in a concatenated string. Should be formatted according to the conventions of the applicable taxonomic discipline.

label: Sex
rdfs_comment: The sex of a specimen. The domain should be a controlled set of terms (codes) based on community consensus. Proposed values: M=Male; F=Female; H=Hermaphrodite; I=Indeterminate (examined but could not be determined; U=Unkown (not examined); T=Transitional (between sexes; useful for sequential hermaphrodites)

label: Sex
rdfs_comment: The sex of a cataloged item (e.g., male, female, hermaphrodite, gynandromorph, not recorded, indeterminate, transitional - between sexes, for sequential hermaphrodites).

label: Species
rdfs_comment: The specific epithet of the organism

label: Species
rdfs_comment: The phylogenetic specific epithet of the cataloged item.

label: State Province
rdfs_comment: The state, province or region (i.e. next political region smaller than Country) from which the specimen was collected. There is some suggestion to use the values described in ISO 3166-2 (http://www.iso.ch/cate/d8349.html), however these values are in a continual state of flux and it appears unlikely that an appropriate mechanism (by ISO) will be in place to manage these changes. Hence it is recommended that where possible, the full, unabbreviated name should be used for storing information. The server should optionally handle abbreviations as an access point. Note: this is a recurring theme (country and state) abbreviations. Check the existence of an attribute type to deal with abbreviations from the bib-1 profile

label: State Province
rdfs_comment: The full, unabbreviated name of the state, province, or region (i.e., the next smaller political region than Country) from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Subspecies
rdfs_comment: The sub-specific epithet of the organism

label: Subspecies
rdfs_comment: The phylogenetic subspecific epithet of the cataloged item.

label: Time Collected
rdfs_comment: The time of day the cataloged item was collected, expressed as decimal hours from midnight, local time (e.g., 12.0 = noon, 13.5 = 1:30pm).

label: Time of Day
rdfs_comment: The time of day a specimen was collected expressed as decimal hours from midnight local time (e.g. 12.0 = mid day, 13.5 = 1:30pm)

label: Tissues
rdfs_comment: A concatenated list of tissues and preservation methods (whole (frozen), liver (EDTA), etc.) for the cataloged item.

label: Type Status
rdfs_comment: Indicates the kind of nomenclatural type that a specimen represents. (This is incomplete because type status actually describes the relationship between a name and a specimen [or ternary relatiohnship between a specimen, name, and publication].) In particular, the type status may not apply to the name listed in the scientific name, i.e., current identification. In rare cases, a single specimen may be the type of more than one name.

label: Type Status
rdfs_comment: A list of one or more nomenclatural types that the cataloged item represents (e.g., "holotype of Ctenomys sociabilis. Pearson O. P., and M. I. Christie. 1985. Historia Natural, 5(37):388.").

label: Verbatim Collecting Date
rdfs_comment: The verbatim original representation of the date information for the collecting event.

label: Verbatim Depth
rdfs_comment: A text representation of the Depth in its original format in the source database.

label: Verbatim Elevation
rdfs_comment: A text representation of the Elevation in its original format in the source database.

label: Verbatim Latitude
rdfs_comment: A text representation of the Latitude data in its original format in the source database.

label: Verbatim Longitude
rdfs_comment: A text representation of the Longitude data in its original format in the source database.

label: Year Collected
rdfs_comment: The year (expressed as an integer) in which the specimen was collected. The full year should be expressed (e.g. 1972 must be expressed as "1972" not "72"). Must always be a four digit integer [-9999..9999]

label: Year Collected
rdfs_comment: The four digit year in the Common Era calendar in which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Year Identified
rdfs_comment: The year portion of the date when the Collection Item was identified; as four digits [-9999..9999], e.g., 1906, 2002.

label: Year Identified
rdfs_comment: The four digit year in the Common Era calendar in which the cataloged item was identified as having the ScientificName.

label: Bed
rdfs_comment: The full name of the lithostratigraphic bed from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Earliest Age Or Lowest Stage
rdfs_comment: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic age or lowest chronostratigraphic stage attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Earliest Eon Or Lowest Eonothem
rdfs_comment: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic eon or lowest chrono-stratigraphic eonothem or the informal name ("Precambrian") attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Earliest Epoch Or Lowest Series
rdfs_comment: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic epoch or lowest chronostratigraphic series attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Earliest Era Or Lowest Erathem
rdfs_comment: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic era or lowest chronostratigraphic erathem attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Earliest Period Or Lowest System
rdfs_comment: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic period or lowest chronostratigraphic system attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Formation
rdfs_comment: The full name of the lithostratigraphic formation from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Group
rdfs_comment: The full name of the lithostratigraphic group from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Highest Biostratigraphic Zone
rdfs_comment: The full name of the highest possible geological biostratigraphic zone of the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Latest AgeOr Highest Stage
rdfs_comment: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic age or highest chronostratigraphic stage attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Latest Eon Or Highest Eonothem
rdfs_comment: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic eon or highest chrono-stratigraphic eonothem or the informal name ("Precambrian") attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Latest Epoch Or Highest Series
rdfs_comment: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic epoch or highest chronostratigraphic series attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Latest Era Or Highest Erathem
rdfs_comment: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic era or highest chronostratigraphic erathem attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Latest Period Or Highest System
rdfs_comment: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic period or highest chronostratigraphic system attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Lithostratigraphic Terms
rdfs_comment: The combination of all litho-stratigraphic names for the rock from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Lowest Biostratigraphic Zone
rdfs_comment: The full name of the lowest possible geological biostratigraphic zone of the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: Member
rdfs_comment: The full name of the lithostratigraphic member from which the cataloged item was collected.

label: source material identifiers
rdfs_comment: A unique identifier assigned to a material sample (as defined by http://rs-test.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/MaterialSampleID, and as opposed to a particular digital record of a material sample) used for extracting nucleic acids, and subsequent sequencing. The identifier can refer either to the original material collected or to any derived sub-samples. The INSDC qualifiers /specimen_voucher, /bio_material, or /culture_collection provide additional context and suggested syntax for this identifier for data submitted to INSDC databases.
